{"author":{"id":"d3ab03f5937173cbce628928f26a71404423aa1354b00b4bab1ed6d6046d035b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1539758084,"nonce":"sZAdi1SR8ie2CrAO7YBHXgj1HGo=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUzNzA5MTg1OTk=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/2143","origin":"github"},"title":"trinity bug","message":"hello\nTrinity galaxy tool:\nThis affects all the version of Trinity 2.4.0 including the latest one 21 / ca0588b09438\n\nPreviously Trinity only did read normalisation if the --normalize_reads option was provided. This is no longer the case.\n\nTrinity 2.4.0 does read normalisation by default. \n\nIt uses the optional flag --no_normalize_reads to NOT normalise the reads. The galaxy tools use an older option that expected --normalize_reads to normalise the reads. \n\nThis means that all galaxy runs with users that set normalisation to FALSE, always got their data normalised anyway ...\n\nThe correct xml line would be:\n\n`\n\u003cparam name=\"norm\" type=\"boolean\" argument=\"--no_normalize_reads\" truevalue=\"\" falsevalue=\"--no_normalize_reads\" checked=\"true\" label=\"Run in silico normalization of reads\" help=\"Defaults to max. read coverage of 50.\"/\u003e\n`\n[so i can't do a diff any time soon...]\na","files":null}]}